<item>
            <title>[SOLR-876] Add ability to optionally splitOnNumerics WordDelimiterFilter/Factory</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-876</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Add ability to optionally splitOnNumerics WordDelimiterFilter/Factory&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Default behaviour is to splitOnNumerics as WordDelimiterFilter/Factory does now&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I was having issues with e.g. Java/J2SE becoming split into tokens &apos;Java&apos;,&apos;J&apos; &apos;2&apos; and &apos;SE&apos;  which isn&apos;t desired behavior in my instance, I wanted this to be tokens &apos;Java&apos;, &apos;J2SE&apos;. Another option I thought about but not implemented was to have a protected list of words like solr.EnglishPorterFilterFactory&lt;/p&gt;</description>
